  "prompt": "Can I eat food which has already been eaten by red ants?",
  "response": "Eating food that has been in contact with red ants is generally not recommended. While red ants are not known to carry harmful pathogens that pose a significant risk to humans, they can carry bacteria and other microorganisms from their environment. Additionally, ant bites or stings can cause allergic reactions or irritation. \n\nIf the food is still in good condition and the ants have only come into contact with it briefly, you may choose to wash it thoroughly and then consume it. However, if the food is heavily infested or has been significantly contaminated, it is best to discard it to avoid any potential health risks. Always prioritize food safety and hygiene.",
